[SN]TITLE[SN]
Wolves: Jon Dadi Bodvarsson and Joao Teixeira join Championship club

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Wolves have signed Jon Dadi Bodvarsson from Kaiserslautern on a three-year deal and midfielder Joao Teixeira from Benfica on a season-long loan.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Striker Bodvarsson, 24, who has made 26 appearances for Iceland, scored for them at Euro 2016, against Austria.
Teixeira, 22, has predominantly featured for Benfica's B team in the Portuguese second tier.
His only first-team appearance for Benfica came in the Champions League against Bayer Leverkusen in 2014.
The pair follow the signings of winger Helder Costa from Benfica and Atletico Madrid defender Silvio, for an undisclosed fee, which were completed either side of Kenny Jackett being replaced as head coach by Walter Zenga.
